### 9 Marker: Multiplier and Circular Flow (Q3)
An injection is an addition to the circular flow (I, X, G). Withdrawals include M, S, T. The multiplier is the process by which injections lead to multiple increases in GDP.

Suppose exports increase by £100m. Factor incomes increase by £100m in the first round. If MPC is 0.5 then £50m is lost through leakages. Firms face a further £50m increase in AD. GDP increase is now £150m. Next round: £25m lost through leakages, GDP increase is £175m. The process continues until a new equilibrium. The multiplier is 1/(1-MPC) = 2. So £100m in exports leads to £200m increase in GDP.

