### 15 Marker: Causes of Inflation (Q13, 2019 Paper)

**Question:** Explain the main causes of inflation. (15 marks)

**Point 1 – Demand-pull:** When AD increases, excess demand at the original price level occurs. Firms face increasing MC but buoyant AD allows MR to increase, so prices rise. Beyond full employment, scarce factors of production push wages and prices higher.

**Point 2 – Cost-push:** Increasing raw material costs (e.g. from depreciation) shift SRAS left. Higher production costs mean firms produce less at each price level. Shortage at original price level causes prices to rise. In an open economy like the UK with complex supply chains, this effect is strong.

**Point 3 – Role of MPC:** Whether pressures result in actual inflation depends on MPC actions and effectiveness. Interest rate changes take 18+ months to work through. If inflation is not accurately predicted or concerns make rate increases less likely, inflation is more likely to occur.

