### 15 Marker: Positive Output Gap Problems (June 2022)

**Question:** Explain the main problems of having a large positive output gap. (15 marks)

**Point 1 – Wage-price spiral:** Rising prices with low wages mean lower disposable incomes. Workers ask for higher wages. If firms accept, they may raise prices further or lay off workers.

**Point 2 – Worsening current account:** If UK prices rise while stable abroad, consumers import more and foreigners buy less UK output. Trade balance (X-M) worsens. This is one of the four main macroeconomic objectives.

