### 9 Marker: Tariffs and Imports (June 2020)

A tariff is a tax on imports. World supply is perfectly elastic. A tariff shifts world supply left, price rises from p1 to p2. Contraction along domestic demand, expansion along domestic supply. Domestic output increases from q1 to q3. Volume of imports falls from q1-q2 to q3-q4.

